1
00:01:35,850 --> 00:01:38,240
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:41,350
[Episode 7]

3
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,120
I'm so happy!

4
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:43,560
How...

5
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:43,960
How...

6
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,560
How did you convince your dad?

7
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:47,070
With Shan's help, of course!

8
00:01:47,070 --> 00:01:49,110
Shan not only got me a cello instructor,

9
00:01:49,110 --> 00:01:50,400
but also persuaded my dad.

10
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,920
How very nice of him.

11
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:53,560
Based on your account of him,

12
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,759
Shan is indeed the best

13
00:01:54,759 --> 00:01:56,490
older friend one could ask for.

14
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,640
You must improve

15
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:59,400
your academic grades during this period.

16
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,640
Or you might miss out on your dream school

17
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,640
due to low scores.

18
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,040
That'll let Shan down.

19
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:05,350
I checked the cutoff score
for Hailan University.

20
00:02:05,350 --> 00:02:06,480
It is pretty high.

21
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,790
I'm counting on you to improve

22
00:02:07,790 --> 00:02:09,590
my grades on academic subjects.

23
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:12,870
Me?

24
00:02:16,490 --> 00:02:19,360
Don't you need to practice the cello
at Shan's place?

25
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,240
I think...

26
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:22,910
during your cello practice there,

27
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,370
you can have him tutor you.

28
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:26,680
But it's been many years
since Shan took the college entrance exam.

29
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,940
He must've forgotten everything by now.

30
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:31,630
I guess so.

31
00:02:34,470 --> 00:02:36,430
Then what about your best friend

32
00:02:36,430 --> 00:02:37,360
Luo Ningzi?

33
00:02:37,470 --> 00:02:38,630
Why not turn to her?

34
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,190
Ning could be helpful.

35
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,460
I can really ask Ning for help!

36
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:47,870
How did that slip my mind?

37
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:52,980
But as I recall,

38
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,800
she lives pretty far away from your home.

39
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,630
Won't that cause inconvenience?

40
00:02:55,630 --> 00:02:56,280
It won't be a problem.

41
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,740
She can tutor me at school.

42
00:03:04,470 --> 00:03:04,910
No.

43
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:07,870
Look,

44
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:12,080
it'll be late by the time you get home
after the tutoring.

45
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,680
Uncle Dong will get worried.

46
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:14,840
So, you should

47
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:16,690
still be tutored by me.

48
00:03:19,470 --> 00:03:21,150
First, you said no to helping me.

49
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:22,910
Then, you offered to tutor me.

50
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:25,630
What exactly is your decision?

51
00:03:25,630 --> 00:03:27,840
Will you... accept my help or not?

52
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:29,000
Fine, fine, fine.

53
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:30,360
Please be my tutor,

54
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,590
my best friend.

55
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,260
You finally realize
who your best friend is.

56
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:40,170
Stop laughing.

57
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:40,840
I'm not laughing.

58
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,840
Stop it now!

59
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:44,240
Knock it off, or I will...

60
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:45,400
Yi Lan!

61
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,240
Stay back!

62
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:49,150
Hurry up.

63
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:50,310
I've been waiting forever.

64
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:51,750
My dream is to marry my idol.

65
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:52,210
A seven!

66
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,780
I've got this! My turn!

67
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,210
An eight.

68
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:58,430
I wish I could be a traveling cellist.

69
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,750
And my wish...

70
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,280
is very simple.

71
00:04:02,030 --> 00:04:06,280
All I want is to be with the person I love
for ever and ever.

72
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,840
"For ever and ever," huh?

73
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,190
Ning, what's your wish?

74
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:16,190
To be the principal cellist
in a top orchestra.

75
00:04:18,870 --> 00:04:19,560
A flush.

76
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:20,480
You'll pass, right?

77
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:20,940
A joker.

78
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:21,829
Still pass, huh?

79
00:04:21,829 --> 00:04:22,360
A bomb.

80
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,380
All out.

81
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,490
How could we let him win?

82
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:29,070
-Just admit defeat.
-We lost again.

83
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:31,000
Where are the paper strips?

84
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,580
There are many on your faces.

85
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:34,180
Change the punishment then.

86
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,290
Your face...

87
00:04:43,310 --> 00:04:44,240
already has many strips stuck on.

88
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,480
I can only flick your forehead.

89
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,210
Do be gentle.

90
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:49,580
Luo Ningzi.

91
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,720
Dad, I'm home!

92
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,800
You're back, Lan.

93
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,660
Wash your hands. Dinner's ready.

94
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,240
I'm serving

95
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,840
your favorite dishes today.

96
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:09,310
Dad, aren't you just amazing?

97
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:11,510
You're really the best dad in the world.

98
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:12,870
What got into you today?

99
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:14,130
You're being so sweet.

100
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:15,630
Dad.

101
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:17,920
I'm all grown up now.

102
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,680
If you have anything to say to me,

103
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,680
just be frank and speak up.

104
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,680
I'll understand.

105
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,780
Anyway, no matter what you do,

106
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:25,070
I know you love me.

107
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,560
Seems like my daughter
has really grown up.

108
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,430
Lecturing your own dad, huh?

109
00:05:34,090 --> 00:05:35,730
[Class 9, Grade 12]

110
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:42,870
Yi Lan.

111
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,560
Well...

112
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,130
I'm Chen Zhihan from Class 1, Grade 12.

113
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,020
It's okay if you don't know me.

114
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:01,930
This is for you.

115
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:03,560
For me?

116
00:06:04,430 --> 00:06:05,120
Thank you.

117
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:08,680
Well,

118
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,850
are you close with Tong Xiaole?

119
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:12,480
Yes.

120
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:17,070
Please pass this letter on to him.

121
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,560
I got it.

122
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:25,560
Thank you.

123
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,070
I only prepared one cup today.

124
00:06:27,070 --> 00:06:28,870
But I'll buy you yours next time.

125
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,360
Do deliver it.

126
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,420
It's in good hands.

127
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:34,000
Who is she?

128
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,560
A fan of Xiaole's.

129
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:40,920
She seems... to be a good match for him.

130
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,800
Dear friends,

131
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:48,200
I'll soon be off for specialized training.

132
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,200
You might not get to see me at school.

133
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:52,390
Don't miss me too much!

134
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,610
Zhao Zhenghao,
are you going to study abroad as well?

135
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,680
Abroad? No.

136
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,600
Domestic universities
are obviously better.

137
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,360
Luo Ningzi!

138
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,020
When are you going abroad?

139
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:07,390
I'm still preparing.

140
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:08,000
What?

141
00:07:08,780 --> 00:07:10,800
She said she was still preparing.

142
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:14,890
Since everyone's around,

143
00:07:14,890 --> 00:07:16,240
how about a gathering this weekend?

144
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,700
I have an important issue.

145
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:19,510
Sure.

146
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,480
Eyes on me!

147
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:34,920
Look at her.

148
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:35,580
Eyes on her.

149
00:07:35,870 --> 00:07:36,680
Okay, okay.

150
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,310
You are gathered here today

151
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:39,510
to help me buy a ticket

152
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:41,040
to my idol's concert.

153
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:42,870
Now,

154
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,590
the most important thing

155
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,340
is to test the internet speed.

156
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:47,480
Get your phones out.

157
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,210
Have a check.

158
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:48,870
Clear all

159
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:49,870
background apps.

160
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:51,630
Nice internet speed.

161
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:52,450
Cleared.

162
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,360
Cleared.

163
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,190
Good.

164
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:55,240
Then,

165
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:57,110
when I count down from ten,

166
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,000
you will open this page

167
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:01,360
and tap the button like crazy

168
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,000
as the tickets are available for purchase.

169
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:03,870
Click non-stop.

170
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:05,630
I thought it was an important matter
in life.

171
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:06,680
As it turns out, you're just

172
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,240
wasting your life on trifles.

173
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,170
What do you know?

174
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,240
Your idol's not even as handsome as I am.

175
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,560
-Mengmeng, why don't you...
-Zhao Zhenghao!

176
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,430
How dare you speak ill of my idol!

177
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:15,690
Sorry. I was wrong.

178
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,630
Qiao Mengmeng,

179
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:17,800
it'll be time soon.

180
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:18,240
Don't blame us

181
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,640
if you can't get a ticket.

182
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,650
You're off the hook for now!

183
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,860
Alright. Open the page.

184
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:26,550
Opened.

185
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,260
The countdown starts.

186
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,750
Five.

187
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,390
Four.

188
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,200
-Three.
-Three.

189
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:35,440
-Two.
-Two.

190
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:36,669
-One.
-One.

191
00:08:36,669 --> 00:08:37,360
Click it!

192
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,039
Has anyone secured a ticket?

193
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,300
How is that even possible?

194
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,200
The page's not responding.

195
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,390
I'm still trying.

196
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:55,960
It's frozen.

197
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,020
The checkout page!

198
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,510
I'll pay for it with your money.

199
00:08:58,510 --> 00:08:59,510
It's processing.

200
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:02,200
Great.

201
00:09:05,630 --> 00:09:06,790
Why is it so slow?

202
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,400
Is the reception bad?

203
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,640
Try it on the balcony.

204
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,600
Is it worth this much trouble?

205
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,630
My goodness.

206
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:17,200
He's really not handsome.

207
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,300
Mengmeng, did you get the ticket?

208
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,240
What's wrong?

209
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,910
Please don't cry.

210
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:30,320
-Mengmeng.
-There, there.

211
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,320
We'll figure something out for you.

212
00:09:32,550 --> 00:09:33,320
All is fine.

213
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,720
There will be a solution.

214
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:35,510
Don't cry.

215
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:38,670
-This is not your idol's only concert.
-You're really crying?

216
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:39,980
Your idol will hold another concert.

217
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:41,740
You can go to that one.

218
00:09:44,030 --> 00:09:45,720
Do you know any other way

219
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,910
to get a ticket?

220
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,440
How about we buy from a scalper?

221
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:51,360
Yes, a scalper!

222
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,080
Right!

223
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,200
I happen to have a contact,

224
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,320
but he requires face-to-face transaction.

225
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:54,720
That's okay.

226
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,150
I'll pay for you first, alright?

227
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:56,840
Let me see.

228
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,790
Scalped tickets are expensive.

229
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:01,080
Why should we buy any?

230
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,780
It's okay. I'll cover you.

231
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:11,750
You guys are my best friends!

232
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:15,000
There, there.

233
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:22,320
I have arrived.

234
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:24,080
Regardless of any opinion,

235
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,440
Yu is always the champion!

236
00:10:26,670 --> 00:10:29,060
Regardless of any opinion,

237
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,670
Yu is always the champion!

238
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,000
Miss!

239
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,320
Did you ask for a ticket?

240
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:35,720
Yes.

241
00:10:37,410 --> 00:10:38,440
It was hard to snag such a ticket.

242
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,120
Thank you.

243
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:39,720
The concert's about to start.

244
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,390
Get in the venue now.

245
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,200
Sure. Thanks!

246
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:43,030
Regardless of any opinion,

247
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,440
Yu is always the champion!

248
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:54,910
Did you deliberately cross my answers?

249
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:57,040
How could I have made so many mistakes?

250
00:10:58,150 --> 00:11:00,080
This angle is 45 degrees.

251
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:02,320
Look carefully.

252
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:06,840
Why are math problems so difficult?

253
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:09,200
Why is my brain so slow?

254
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,360
Why hit your head?

255
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,770
What if you really knock yourself stupid?

256
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:18,600
Hello?

257
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:20,720
Okay, wait a moment.

258
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:21,780
I‘ll be right down.

259
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,750
I'm going to get the takeout.

260
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:24,960
Stop hitting your head.

261
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,420
It might take a toll on you.

262
00:12:01,270 --> 00:12:02,200
Why set an alarm

263
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:03,280
in broad daylight?

264
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,410
What are you looking at?

265
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,920
You folded my wishes into paper cranes?

266
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,870
Who says they are yours?

267
00:12:47,790 --> 00:12:49,270
Not mine?

268
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:51,680
Then you must've imitated me

269
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,180
and written your wishes on paper.

270
00:12:54,910 --> 00:12:55,630
However...

271
00:12:55,790 --> 00:12:58,670
paper cranes are usually girl stuff.

272
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:03,030
Do you...

273
00:13:03,030 --> 00:13:04,430
have a crush on some girl?

274
00:13:06,510 --> 00:13:07,080
Who is she?

275
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:07,720
Tell me!

276
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:09,270
Cut it out.

277
00:13:09,910 --> 00:13:11,670
Some things are better said in person.

278
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:12,790
Why write a letter?

279
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,080
Girls always find it embarrassing

280
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,810
to confess their love for boys.

281
00:13:18,510 --> 00:13:19,240
That's true.

282
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:22,750
Well...

283
00:13:24,510 --> 00:13:26,170
When did this affection grow?

284
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:29,590
Read the letter and you'll know.

285
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,960
If I determine it to be badly written,

286
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,760
I may have a negative impression

287
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,440
of this girl.

288
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,570
She wrote it with all her heart.

289
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:45,320
You should at least read it.

290
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:46,600
Fine.

291
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:48,910
Be quick.

292
00:13:54,910 --> 00:13:56,080
I hope you won't regret it.

293
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:56,840
Regret what?

294
00:14:01,610 --> 00:14:03,560
[Chen Zhihan]

295
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:04,840
Chen Zhihan?

296
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:06,870
She seemed sincere to me.

297
00:14:06,870 --> 00:14:08,450
Why not consider giving her a chance?

298
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:09,360
No way.

299
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,320
The food's here?

300
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:27,510
Leave it there. I'll pack it myself.

301
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,720
I need that pen for later.

302
00:14:31,790 --> 00:14:32,790
It's not done yet.

303
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:35,240
I have yet to finish that paper.

304
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:36,250
What's with you?

305
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,080
The alarm just went off, right?

306
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,210
It's time for my nap.

307
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,440
Are you angry?

308
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:44,710
Why would I be angry?

309
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,670
Just say no to her if you don't like her.

310
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:48,320
What does this have to do with me?

311
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,670
I only delivered her letter to you.

312
00:14:49,670 --> 00:14:50,360
Leave!

313
00:14:50,550 --> 00:14:51,840
I did nothing but give you her letter!

314
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:54,970
-You promised to explain that paper to me!
-I need my nap!

315
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,080
Let go.

316
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,080
Why are you so moody?

317
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,320
We had a deal!

318
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:04,910
Three, two, one.

319
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,320
-I'm not going anywhere!
-Leave!

320
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:08,150
I insist on staying here!

321
00:15:08,150 --> 00:15:08,840
Let go now!

322
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:09,500
The food...

323
00:15:09,790 --> 00:15:11,200
I haven't eaten it yet!

324
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:12,350
Just a second!

325
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:14,200
Let go of me!

326
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,200
Wait, wait, wait!

327
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:15,960
Wait!

328
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,670
I just got a message.

329
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:23,380
[Yi Lan, the concert ticket is fake]

330
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:26,440
Mengmeng!

331
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:27,630
Here I come.

332
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,440
How is it a fake ticket?

333
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,500
Maybe try it again?

334
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:32,790
I had it scanned.

335
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:34,600
Nothing came up.

336
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:36,510
The staff wouldn't let me in.

337
00:15:36,830 --> 00:15:38,960
Look, I'll go ask about this ticket.

338
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,090
You girls wait here.

339
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:40,840
Okay.

340
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,270
Listen!

341
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:50,390
The concert has begun.

342
00:15:50,390 --> 00:15:51,320
It's actually nice to sit here

343
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,650
and hear your idol sing.

344
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:57,850
♪ Watching your profile draw near,
I smile like a fool ♪

345
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,510
This is his debut song.

346
00:15:57,510 --> 00:15:59,550
When my parents were fighting
and getting divorced,

347
00:15:58,310 --> 00:16:02,460
♪ Every word you said, like a melody,
sprouts in my heart ♪

348
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:02,390
listening to his songs was the only way
I could sleep.

349
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:03,600
Didn't I already show it to you?

350
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:06,650
♪ The sparks between us
burn bright within the notes ♪

351
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,840
So what was the big deal?

352
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:05,970
It was just a dinner.

353
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:08,030
It was not like...

354
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:08,950
♪ I look forward ♪

355
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:10,080
I had it with her alone.

356
00:16:08,980 --> 00:16:10,810
♪ To hearing your answer ♪

357
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,440
Lots of people were there as well.

358
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:13,850
♪ My heart won't stop its racing beat ♪

359
00:16:11,910 --> 00:16:13,510
But you two give off a different vibe.

360
00:16:13,510 --> 00:16:14,670
What vibe?

361
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:16,140
♪ The sweetness when our eyes meet ♪

362
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:16,100
We've been married for years!

363
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:16,790
Look,

364
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:20,710
♪ Each time we meet,
it's as if the dream goes on ♪

365
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:17,440
you wouldn't let me eat

366
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:17,910
with anyone.

367
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:18,440
What...

368
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:19,390
What do you want from me?

369
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:20,760
You lack a sense of boundaries...

370
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,900
♪ How I wish to tell you ♪

371
00:16:21,910 --> 00:16:23,550
Come to think of it,

372
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:25,310
♪ It's not a coincidence or a miracle ♪

373
00:16:24,390 --> 00:16:26,440
it seems like he helped me through many,

374
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:29,530
♪ It's destiny ♪

375
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,480
many lonely days.

376
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:32,230
♪ Sharing my earbuds with you ♪

377
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:34,390
♪ Connecting you to my heartbeat ♪

378
00:16:34,450 --> 00:16:36,860
♪ Scrolling up and down the playlist ♪

379
00:16:36,790 --> 00:16:37,910
Mengmeng, I'm sorry.

380
00:16:36,890 --> 00:16:39,820
♪ Disrupting the rhythm of my breath ♪

381
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:39,570
None of us got a ticket for you.

382
00:16:39,950 --> 00:16:41,900
♪ Listen to the same song on repeat ♪

383
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,030
I'm sorry too.

384
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:42,000
I messed it up, though I meant well.

385
00:16:41,930 --> 00:16:43,610
♪ Reveal the secret that should be kept ♪

386
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:43,870
Why apologize at all?

387
00:16:43,690 --> 00:16:46,270
♪ The smile at the corner of your lips ♪

388
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,270
Without you guys,

389
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:46,550
I wouldn't have had fun.

390
00:16:46,290 --> 00:16:48,880
♪ Makes me wonder ♪

391
00:16:47,930 --> 00:16:49,320
We didn't get a ticket anyway.

392
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:51,160
♪ Has Cupid ♪

393
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,190
It's nice to sit here and listen.

394
00:16:51,190 --> 00:16:53,960
♪ Finally shot a golden arrow at you? ♪

395
00:16:57,010 --> 00:16:57,750
It's him!

396
00:16:57,910 --> 00:16:59,080
The man in a black hat!

397
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,390
He sold me a fake ticket!

398
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:01,150
You fraud!

399
00:17:01,150 --> 00:17:01,600
Stay!

400
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,080
Freeze!

401
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:02,720
Halt!

402
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,680
You damn scammer!

403
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:05,550
Stop there!

404
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:06,609
Don't you run away!

405
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:13,160
Stop running!

406
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:13,920
Stop!

407
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,550
His hat...

408
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,310
The hat!

409
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:29,860
Come down here!

410
00:17:32,070 --> 00:17:33,270
Put his pants back on!

411
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:38,550
-Have you caught him?
-Run, I dare you.

412
00:17:38,550 --> 00:17:39,750
-Go get him!
-Come down here!

413
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:40,880
Pants back on!

414
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,310
-Come down here.
-Why stop running?

415
00:17:42,310 --> 00:17:43,070
Y-Y-You...

416
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:43,790
give it back to me.

417
00:17:43,790 --> 00:17:44,590
Then come down here.

418
00:17:44,590 --> 00:17:46,120
And I'll give it back to you.

419
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,270
You promise?

420
00:17:48,310 --> 00:17:49,570
Better keep your word.

421
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:55,930
Please hear me out.

422
00:17:55,930 --> 00:17:57,720
The ticket I sold her was absolutely real.

423
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,720
She just lost it,

424
00:17:58,720 --> 00:17:59,790
and somehow got a fake one.

425
00:17:59,790 --> 00:18:01,050
What is this nonsense?

426
00:18:01,050 --> 00:18:02,400
We traded in person.

427
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,270
If you dare lie again,

428
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:04,270
I'll beat you up!

429
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:07,110
Look,

430
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:09,310
I'm only running a small business.

431
00:18:09,310 --> 00:18:10,160
How about this?

432
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,020
I have tickets to other concerts.

433
00:18:12,310 --> 00:18:12,840
I will...

434
00:18:13,070 --> 00:18:13,600
offer you

435
00:18:14,310 --> 00:18:15,070
a 90% discount for them,

436
00:18:15,070 --> 00:18:15,640
okay?

437
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,110
A 90% discount?

438
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:19,750
Denied!

439
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,140
We want our money back!

440
00:18:24,550 --> 00:18:27,210
Seems like you've swindled
quite a lot of money.

441
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:31,070
Don't...

442
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:32,410
Don't hurt me...

443
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:33,240
Well...

444
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:35,310
L-Let's talk this out.

445
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:37,270
Save your story

446
00:18:37,590 --> 00:18:38,720
for the police.

447
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:42,000
Here's your hat.

448
00:18:42,310 --> 00:18:43,350
Thanks.

449
00:18:46,070 --> 00:18:46,590
Bye!

450
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:52,240
Tong Xiaole!

451
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,970
What exactly are you mad about?

452
00:19:22,850 --> 00:19:23,510
Lan,

453
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:25,040
what's your target school?

454
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:27,440
I've decided.

455
00:19:27,590 --> 00:19:28,830
I'll apply for a school of communications,

456
00:19:28,830 --> 00:19:30,110
so I can be my idol's agent

457
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:31,840
and make him famous worldwide.

458
00:19:32,350 --> 00:19:33,410
I have faith in you.

459
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:39,080
That's the next lesson.

460
00:19:40,730 --> 00:19:43,470
[Report Card for Grade 12 Monthly Exam]

461
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:10,550
The highest score I've got.

462
00:20:09,370 --> 00:20:11,110
[Report Card for Grade 12 Monthly Exam]

463
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:12,400
Who made it happen?

464
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,310
You made it happen, Mr. Tong!

465
00:20:19,310 --> 00:20:20,110
Seriously?

466
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,500
Are you still mad at me?

467
00:20:22,310 --> 00:20:23,400
But for what?

468
00:20:23,730 --> 00:20:24,350
Tell me.

469
00:20:24,550 --> 00:20:25,480
I'll apologize.

470
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:28,170
Come on, say it.

471
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:31,880
Are those paper cranes the reason?

472
00:20:33,210 --> 00:20:34,340
Or that love letter?

473
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:36,510
-Love letter?
-Love letter?

474
00:20:36,510 --> 00:20:38,040
You wrote her a love letter?

475
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:38,640
You did?

476
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:39,880
And you gave it to her?

477
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,310
What is this nonsense?

478
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:42,750
Wrote who a love letter?

479
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:43,310
Who?

480
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:45,030
If you're asking

481
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:46,550
about the girl he likes,

482
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:48,350
then I think I know something...

483
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:50,000
The girl he likes?

484
00:20:50,270 --> 00:20:51,590
Why didn't you tell me?

485
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:52,930
Spill it now.

486
00:20:54,110 --> 00:20:55,590
This girl is right

487
00:20:55,590 --> 00:20:57,880
before our eyes.

488
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,030
Me?

489
00:21:04,590 --> 00:21:05,270
You like me?

490
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:08,440
Yes.

491
00:21:09,270 --> 00:21:10,000
I like you.

492
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:15,960
Are you crazy?

493
00:21:17,590 --> 00:21:18,790
Don't flatter yourself.

494
00:21:18,790 --> 00:21:20,850
I'd have to be crazy to be into someone

495
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:22,790
like you.

496
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:24,240
Hey, Tong Xiaole,

497
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,350
what do you mean?

498
00:21:26,430 --> 00:21:27,830
Now I'm the one being mad.

499
00:21:32,070 --> 00:21:33,270
To keep my anger at bay,

500
00:21:33,270 --> 00:21:35,530
you'd better tell me who you really like.

501
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:38,790
He is into...

502
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:40,240
Who?

503
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:42,240
Me.

504
00:21:43,030 --> 00:21:43,400
Me.

505
00:21:44,310 --> 00:21:45,640
Quite a bustle here, huh?

506
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:46,310
Xiaole.

507
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:47,690
Come with me.

508
00:21:52,550 --> 00:21:53,680
What does this mean?

509
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,150
Nobody told me the truth.

510
00:21:56,310 --> 00:21:57,040
Spill it now.

511
00:21:57,070 --> 00:21:58,270
We won't tell anyone.

512
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:00,680
All I can tell you

513
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:02,550
is that the answer is obvious,

514
00:22:02,830 --> 00:22:03,960
but cannot be told.

515
00:22:05,110 --> 00:22:06,590
Are we good friends or not?

516
00:22:07,550 --> 00:22:08,240
Xiaole.

517
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:09,810
Have you decided

518
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,070
which university...

519
00:22:11,070 --> 00:22:11,920
to apply for?

520
00:22:14,310 --> 00:22:15,710
Yes, Hailan University.

521
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:18,980
Hailan University...

522
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:21,560
Its computer science...

523
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:24,720
and business management
are top-tier programs.

524
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:26,070
Which major...

525
00:22:26,790 --> 00:22:27,720
will you choose?

526
00:22:29,310 --> 00:22:30,270
As for the major,

527
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:30,720
I...

528
00:22:31,030 --> 00:22:32,400
haven't decided yet.

529
00:22:35,210 --> 00:22:36,010
Xiaole,

530
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:38,160
I understand

531
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:39,960
that your father

532
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:41,490
is a bit too strict with you.

533
00:22:41,510 --> 00:22:42,270
That said,

534
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,770
you should really listen to

535
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,530
your inner voice when you pick a major.

536
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:48,750
I mean,

537
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:49,810
follow your heart.

538
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:50,590
I'm saying that

539
00:22:50,590 --> 00:22:51,960
because with a major

540
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,350
that you really like,

541
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:56,120
at least you'll be happy
in your future life

542
00:22:56,830 --> 00:22:58,070
and studies.

543
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,750
That's what I'd love to see.

544
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:04,210
I heard from your fellows that you're into

545
00:23:04,270 --> 00:23:05,470
photography, right?

546
00:23:07,030 --> 00:23:08,890
It's actually quite a good major.

547
00:23:09,110 --> 00:23:10,270
If you're interested,

548
00:23:10,270 --> 00:23:11,790
I can introduce you to some...

549
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:12,400
Bu,

550
00:23:13,270 --> 00:23:14,310
don't meddle with this.

551
00:23:14,310 --> 00:23:15,570
I'll take my leave now.

552
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:17,600
Do give it some thought!

553
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:23,550
What now?

554
00:23:23,830 --> 00:23:25,830
The principal pressured you again?

555
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:27,830
The acceptance rate

556
00:23:27,830 --> 00:23:29,640
for key universities has decreased
in recent two years.

557
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:30,770
Don't you know that?

558
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:33,160
That boy Tong Xiaole from my class

559
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:35,160
is a top ten student in the province.

560
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:37,030
The principal's eyes are on him every day.

561
00:23:37,030 --> 00:23:38,630
How can I not feel pressured?

562
00:23:38,790 --> 00:23:39,720
Have you heard?

563
00:23:40,270 --> 00:23:41,160
The dean's office

564
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,760
is discussing re-classing.

565
00:23:43,270 --> 00:23:46,070
I don't think you'll be able
to manage Xiaole soon.

566
00:23:54,380 --> 00:23:56,160
[Hailan University of China,
Undergraduate Admission]

567
00:23:56,190 --> 00:23:57,340
[Hailan University of China,
Undergraduate Admission]
[Photography Department]

568
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:11,030
[You have a new message]

569
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,030
Hello, sorry to bother you.

570
00:24:12,110 --> 00:24:14,160
I really like your photography style.

571
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,270
Could you take a family photo

572
00:24:15,270 --> 00:24:16,740
of me and my grandmother?

573
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:17,510
Can we meet up

574
00:24:17,510 --> 00:24:18,720
at your convenience?

575
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,400
My grandmother

576
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:24,400
has Alzheimer's.

577
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,790
She's lucid sometimes,
but confused at others.

578
00:24:26,790 --> 00:24:28,070
She has long forgotten

579
00:24:28,070 --> 00:24:30,130
that my parents already passed away.

580
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:33,040
She's even been mistaking me
for my mother.

581
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:34,490
This is the whole story.

582
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,160
So you're asking me

583
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:38,070
to take a photo of your grandmother,

584
00:24:38,070 --> 00:24:39,480
which is similar to the one

585
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:40,640
you just

586
00:24:41,110 --> 00:24:41,750
showed me?

587
00:24:42,350 --> 00:24:42,750
Yes.

588
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:47,770
I've been working out of town.

589
00:24:47,830 --> 00:24:49,880
My childhood home
has been vacant for a long time.

590
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:50,790
I'm going to stay here

591
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:51,960
for about two weeks.

592
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,240
Will you...

593
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,310
take this job?

594
00:24:56,350 --> 00:24:59,150
You subscribed to my account
some time ago, right?

595
00:25:00,310 --> 00:25:01,160
I bet you are aware

596
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,790
that I don't really like

597
00:25:02,790 --> 00:25:04,550
taking staged photos like that.

598
00:25:04,550 --> 00:25:05,480
Of course I know.

599
00:25:05,790 --> 00:25:08,250
Just take photos in whatever style
you like.

600
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:13,110
Actually, I've been a bit busy

601
00:25:13,110 --> 00:25:14,510
w-w-with

602
00:25:14,510 --> 00:25:15,590
my studies lately.

603
00:25:16,030 --> 00:25:17,350
Why not hire someone else to...

604
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:18,410
It's not a problem.

605
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,020
We can work around your schedule.

606
00:25:22,310 --> 00:25:23,200
In fact,

607
00:25:24,310 --> 00:25:26,350
I've been your fan for quite some time.

608
00:25:26,350 --> 00:25:28,270
I didn't expect you to be so young.

609
00:25:28,830 --> 00:25:30,510
I really love the feeling

610
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:32,110
that your photos convey,

611
00:25:33,350 --> 00:25:35,550
especially the one in your pinned post.

612
00:25:36,310 --> 00:25:37,710
Is that your girlfriend?

613
00:25:38,830 --> 00:25:39,350
No, no.

614
00:25:39,350 --> 00:25:40,160
She's not.

615
00:25:46,350 --> 00:25:47,270
How about this?

616
00:25:47,270 --> 00:25:49,000
Send me the photo,

617
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:50,790
and I will...

618
00:25:51,110 --> 00:25:52,110
think about it.

619
00:25:52,310 --> 00:25:52,790
Okay.

620
00:25:52,870 --> 00:25:54,330
I'll wait to hear from you.

621
00:26:07,750 --> 00:26:09,080
What are you looking at?

622
00:26:19,070 --> 00:26:20,000
Come on.

623
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,790
I bought you cake.

624
00:26:21,790 --> 00:26:22,960
Stop being mad, okay?

625
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:24,160
I won't do that again.

626
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:28,440
It was a mistake.

627
00:26:29,110 --> 00:26:29,960
What was the mistake?

628
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:32,090
That I sent you someone's love letter.

629
00:26:34,070 --> 00:26:36,000
Have you ever had a crush on anyone?

630
00:26:36,270 --> 00:26:37,730
Are you looking down at me?

631
00:26:37,830 --> 00:26:38,590
So what if I've never

632
00:26:38,590 --> 00:26:39,790
had a crush on anyone?

633
00:26:41,750 --> 00:26:42,680
Why take it away?

634
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,310
The girl who you just talked to

635
00:26:47,310 --> 00:26:48,720
seemed quite nice.

636
00:26:49,070 --> 00:26:51,670
Is she the girl
mentioned in your paper cranes?

637
00:26:51,830 --> 00:26:53,880
She is pretty, isn't she?

638
00:26:56,590 --> 00:26:58,790
How come you've never told me about her?

639
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,030
Well...

640
00:27:10,790 --> 00:27:12,880
She's this madam's granddaughter.

641
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:14,960
She just asked me to take a family photo

642
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:17,070
of her and her grandmother like this one.

643
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:17,790
Sounds lovely.

644
00:27:17,790 --> 00:27:18,850
When will you do it?

645
00:27:21,270 --> 00:27:22,510
I'm not sure if I'll do it.

646
00:27:22,510 --> 00:27:23,160
Why not?

647
00:27:24,270 --> 00:27:27,350
I think... an important photo like this

648
00:27:28,070 --> 00:27:29,070
should be taken

649
00:27:29,070 --> 00:27:30,800
by someone more professional.

650
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,640
Have some confidence in yourself, alright?

651
00:27:32,640 --> 00:27:33,900
You take great photos.

652
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:44,480
Hello?

653
00:27:44,830 --> 00:27:46,360
Hey, Xiaole, where are you?

654
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,180
We're already downstairs at your place.

655
00:27:50,790 --> 00:27:51,640
So it means

656
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:53,750
everyone in this family photo is gone,

657
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:55,810
except Xiaorou and her grandmother?

658
00:27:55,960 --> 00:27:57,240
Her grandmother has no idea

659
00:27:57,240 --> 00:28:00,300
that her daughter and son-in-law
already passed away.

660
00:28:01,030 --> 00:28:02,270
That's so sad.

661
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,440
We can do a role play.

662
00:28:07,830 --> 00:28:09,790
Perhaps it'll jog

663
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:11,510
her grandmother's memory.

664
00:28:11,960 --> 00:28:13,020
That's a good idea!

665
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,960
Xiaorou has indeed encountered
a harsh reality.

666
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,400
But do we have time to help her?

667
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,400
Exams are coming up,

668
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,720
and our grades are terrible.

669
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:20,550
If I fail again,

670
00:28:20,550 --> 00:28:21,950
my mom won't be nice to me.

671
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,550
The time is pressing,

672
00:28:23,550 --> 00:28:24,400
but Xiaorou

673
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:26,000
desperately needs our help.

674
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:28,310
Plus, Xiaole is a great photographer.

675
00:28:28,310 --> 00:28:30,170
I'm sure he'd love to contribute.

676
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:40,000
Stop trying to be a savior.

677
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,460
Respect everyone's fate.

678
00:28:41,830 --> 00:28:43,360
This is Xiaole's business.

679
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:47,110
Well...

680
00:28:47,590 --> 00:28:48,830
Will you help?

681
00:28:52,790 --> 00:28:55,480
I... am not sure.

682
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:58,110
How about... we hold a vote?

683
00:28:58,640 --> 00:28:59,480
Wait a minute.

684
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:02,070
This is my own business.

685
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,160
Letting you vote on it

686
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:07,070
makes me look utterly indecisive.

687
00:29:07,070 --> 00:29:08,600
You are really indecisive.

688
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:11,880
But we're a team.

689
00:29:12,070 --> 00:29:13,510
Yes, we are a team.

690
00:29:13,510 --> 00:29:15,240
Your business is our business.

691
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:17,350
Don't stand on ceremony, lad.

692
00:29:18,270 --> 00:29:19,160
Hello!

693
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:22,240
-Zhao Zhenghao?
-You all missed me a lot, didn't you?

694
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:23,070
You came at the perfect time.

695
00:29:23,070 --> 00:29:24,400
Let me ask you something.

696
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,640
We'd like to help a stranger

697
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,640
fulfill her wish.

698
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,550
Are you for or against it?

699
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,070
Say what now?

700
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:33,880
Give me an answer.

701
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:34,790
That sounds fun.

702
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:35,880
Okay, three to two. We win.

703
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:36,790
What "three to two"?

704
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:38,850
Zhao Zhenghao's vote doesn't count.

705
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:39,960
He has joined us

706
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:40,750
in so many events.

707
00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:42,640
-Do you still not see him one of us?
-Wait.

708
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:43,570
What do you mean?

709
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:45,640
Have I never been taken seriously?

710
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:46,310
Fine, I'm leaving then.

711
00:29:46,310 --> 00:29:48,070
You're of course
an important member of ours.

712
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:49,470
Your vote surely counts.

713
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,880
Tong Xiaole's vote is also valid.

714
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,070
As the person involved,

715
00:29:53,070 --> 00:29:54,110
he doesn't get to vote.

716
00:29:54,110 --> 00:29:55,590
It's a tie, three to three.

717
00:29:55,590 --> 00:29:56,790
Though he appears reluctant,

718
00:29:56,790 --> 00:29:57,640
he actually wants to do it.

719
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,790
He just hates for us to interfere.

720
00:29:58,790 --> 00:29:59,640
Enough!

721
00:29:59,830 --> 00:30:00,790
Wait. What's going on?

722
00:30:00,790 --> 00:30:01,750
Quiet down.

723
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:03,270
This discussion has nothing

724
00:30:03,270 --> 00:30:05,070
to do with the one we had earlier.

725
00:30:05,350 --> 00:30:06,400
Don't waste time.

726
00:30:10,550 --> 00:30:11,410
How about this?

727
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:12,600
I'll do it.

728
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:14,480
Listen,

729
00:30:14,750 --> 00:30:16,400
next Friday after school,

730
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:18,080
come join me if you're free.

731
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:20,160
Now, all of you are

732
00:30:20,590 --> 00:30:21,520
satisfied, huh?

733
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:26,260
What happened?

734
00:30:27,790 --> 00:30:28,720
Care to explain?

735
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,260
[Class 9, Grade 12]

736
00:30:59,030 --> 00:31:00,160
It's so dark in here.

737
00:31:00,750 --> 00:31:01,790
Dusty, too.

738
00:31:02,790 --> 00:31:04,070
So much dust around.

739
00:31:12,830 --> 00:31:14,360
How long until they arrive?

740
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:15,510
Let me check.

741
00:31:17,550 --> 00:31:19,610
Xiaorou said it'd take one more hour.

742
00:31:19,750 --> 00:31:20,750
We need to restore this place

743
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:22,310
to how it used to look, right?

744
00:31:22,310 --> 00:31:22,750
Yeah.

745
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:24,790
Then... let's get to work.

746
00:31:25,270 --> 00:31:25,790
Okay.

747
00:31:36,070 --> 00:31:38,160
It looks quite decent!

748
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:39,730
What do you think, guys?

749
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:40,720
You look good.

750
00:31:40,720 --> 00:31:41,520
Just alright.

751
00:31:41,830 --> 00:31:43,830
The only similarity is your outfit.

752
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:44,830
It's fine.

753
00:31:44,830 --> 00:31:46,310
If that old lady mistakes Xiaorou
for her daughter,

754
00:31:46,310 --> 00:31:48,770
then she'll probably mistake me
for her son.

755
00:31:49,590 --> 00:31:50,270
Chen Fan.

756
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:53,560
You look quite like the part.

757
00:31:53,790 --> 00:31:54,960
Why did you bring me

758
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:56,310
to the old house?

759
00:31:58,030 --> 00:31:59,830
Why are there so many people?

760
00:32:01,270 --> 00:32:02,590
This is the photographer I hired.

761
00:32:02,590 --> 00:32:03,070
He will

762
00:32:03,070 --> 00:32:04,130
take photos for us.

763
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:05,040
Hello, ma'am.

764
00:32:06,790 --> 00:32:08,190
Why are you all standing?

765
00:32:08,310 --> 00:32:09,020
Have a seat.

766
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,030
Be seated.

767
00:32:10,110 --> 00:32:10,640
Sit down.

768
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:11,070
Okay.

769
00:32:12,110 --> 00:32:13,550
This is my son's outfit.

770
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:16,160
Why are you wearing my son's outfit?

771
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:17,550
He's wearing my son's outfit!

772
00:32:17,550 --> 00:32:19,240
I am your son's colleague.

773
00:32:19,310 --> 00:32:20,910
I have the same outfit as him.

774
00:32:22,070 --> 00:32:23,480
He said he missed you a lot,

775
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,510
so he sent us here in particular

776
00:32:24,510 --> 00:32:25,400
to take a photo of you.

777
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:26,860
He'd love to see your face.

778
00:32:27,510 --> 00:32:28,240
What...

779
00:32:28,510 --> 00:32:29,590
What did you say?

780
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:31,790
My son missed me?

781
00:32:31,790 --> 00:32:32,920
-Yes, a lot.
-Right.

782
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:33,740
Yes.

783
00:32:33,750 --> 00:32:35,590
My son missed me...

784
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:36,560
Hurry.

785
00:32:36,590 --> 00:32:37,350
-Ma'am...
-Hurry!

786
00:32:37,350 --> 00:32:38,550
Take a photo of me!

787
00:32:38,570 --> 00:32:40,160
-Take a photo of me now!
-Ma'am, stand here.

788
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:40,640
Well,

789
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:41,640
do I look fine?

790
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:42,510
Is my outfit okay?

791
00:32:42,510 --> 00:32:43,350
-You look great!
-You look great!

792
00:32:43,350 --> 00:32:44,160
Really?

793
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:45,640
Look here, ma'am.

794
00:32:45,790 --> 00:32:46,830
Three, two, one.

795
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,450
Thank you so much.

796
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:53,070
Grandma passed away peacefully.

797
00:32:53,070 --> 00:32:53,640
Really,

798
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,790
thank you for breaking your rule

799
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:58,450
and taking this last photo
of my grandmother.

800
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:00,830
Xiaole!

801
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,310
Xiaole!

802
00:33:02,830 --> 00:33:03,400
Dad.

803
00:33:03,590 --> 00:33:04,190
Come here.

804
00:33:04,750 --> 00:33:06,240
Mom and Dad are back.

805
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:07,880
Did you miss us?

806
00:33:08,310 --> 00:33:08,720
Yes.

807
00:33:08,790 --> 00:33:10,030
Look what I bought you.

808
00:33:10,030 --> 00:33:11,480
A camera!

809
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,160
Take photos with it from now on, okay?

810
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:13,550
Okay.

811
00:33:13,550 --> 00:33:14,480
Let's try it out.

812
00:33:14,550 --> 00:33:14,960
Sure.

813
00:33:16,830 --> 00:33:17,790
Alright. One, two, three.

814
00:33:17,790 --> 00:33:18,550
Up you go!

815
00:33:18,550 --> 00:33:19,350
Up you go!

816
00:33:20,070 --> 00:33:21,110
Let me get you up!

817
00:33:21,510 --> 00:33:22,310
Xiaole,

818
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:23,790
what fish is this?

819
00:33:24,310 --> 00:33:25,480
Catfish.

820
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:26,270
Yes, catfish.

821
00:33:26,270 --> 00:33:27,350
Come over here.

822
00:33:27,350 --> 00:33:28,510
What fish is this?

823
00:33:28,510 --> 00:33:29,550
Grass carp.

824
00:33:31,310 --> 00:33:32,400
What is this then?

825
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:34,550
Purple-spotted tonguefish.

826
00:33:34,650 --> 00:33:35,450
[Purple-spotted Tonguefish]

827
00:33:36,110 --> 00:33:36,790
Impressive.

828
00:33:36,790 --> 00:33:39,310
Xiaole, what fish do you like to eat?

829
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:42,260
[Purple-spotted Tonguefish]

830
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,000
Sharks.

831
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:46,750
Xiaole,

832
00:33:47,110 --> 00:33:49,170
how about you like eating grass crap?

833
00:34:02,860 --> 00:34:07,400
[Pre-filled College Application
Preference Form]

834
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:20,800
Mom,

835
00:34:21,290 --> 00:34:22,730
have you had dinner yet?
